*.bin filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Only the 465MB full pool stays in Git LFS; the small demo pools (sample, 1k,
# *_rand_*) are plain git so Streamlit Cloud clones them without LFS bandwidth.
# The full pool is excluded from the default LFS fetch via .lfsconfig, so a normal
# clone pulls only its pointer (~130B). Materialise it when needed (Stage-3 / re-
# precompute) with:  git lfs pull --include="assets/candidates/100k_pool.jsonl"
assets/candidates/100k_pool.jsonl filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text